-# Locals: employee_name, manager_name, collapse_id (optional)
- employee_name = local_assigns[:employee_name]
- manager_name = local_assigns[:manager_name]
- collapse_id = local_assigns.fetch(:collapse_id, 'finalizationAssignmentEnergyHelp')

.row.mb-2
  .col-12
    %span.d-inline-flex.align-items-center.gap-1.small.text-muted
      %span{"data-bs-toggle" => "tooltip", "data-bs-placement" => "top", "data-bs-title" => "How to read the energy bars. Click for details."}
        %button.btn.btn-link.btn-sm.p-0.text-body{type: 'button', "data-bs-toggle" => "collapse", "data-bs-target" => "##{collapse_id}", "aria-expanded" => "false", "aria-controls" => collapse_id, "aria-label" => "Show energy bar explanation"}
          %i.bi.bi-info-circle
      Energy bar guide

.collapse.mb-2{id: collapse_id}
  .alert.alert-light.border.mb-0.small
    %p.mb-2
      %strong Goal:
      See how #{employee_name}'s Assignment-energy is split across active tenures today and how the updated forecast will look after finalization.
    %p.mb-2
      %strong Example:
      If #{employee_name} reflected 40% on one assignment and 30% on another, the
      %strong current
      bar shows that reflection. If a third assignment still uses only the tenure forecast (20%), that slice appears from the forecast until #{employee_name} completes a reflection.
    %ul.mb-2
      %li
        %strong Current Assignment-energy split (left):
        Starts with every active tenure assignment; replaces a slice with #{employee_name}'s completed reflection when an open check-in overrides that assignment.
      %li
        %strong Updated forecast (right):
        Matches the left bar unless an assignment is ready for finalization—then uses the finalization energy % #{manager_name} sets below. Totals should land near 100%.
      %li
        %span.d-inline-block.me-1{style: 'width: 0.75rem; height: 0.75rem; background: var(--bs-success); border-radius: 2px;'}
        Border at 100% —
        %span.d-inline-block.me-1{style: 'width: 0.75rem; height: 0.75rem; background: var(--bs-warning); border-radius: 2px;'}
        near 90–110% —
        %span.d-inline-block.me-1{style: 'width: 0.75rem; height: 0.75rem; background: var(--bs-danger); border-radius: 2px;'}
        otherwise.
    %p.mb-0.text-muted
      Hover a colored slice for assignment name, current forecast, #{employee_name}'s actual reflection, and new forecast. The right bar updates when forecast % selects change below; values save when you finalize.
